Note:
compiler/backend/bytecode_gen/instruction_set.runa
Bytecode Instruction Set Definition

This module provides comprehensive bytecode instruction set functionality including:
- Complete bytecode instruction set definition and encoding
- Instruction opcode assignment and categorization
- Operand encoding and decoding specifications
- Instruction format definitions and validation
- Stack effect computation for each instruction
- Instruction execution semantics documentation
- AOTT-specific instruction extensions
- Profiling and deoptimization instruction support
- Platform-specific instruction variants
- Instruction set evolution and versioning
- Instruction scheduling and dependency information
- Performance characteristics of each instruction
- Integration with runtime execution engine
- Bytecode verification instruction support
:End Note

Import "dev/debug/errors/core" as Errors

Note: =====================================================================
Note: INSTRUCTION SET DATA STRUCTURES
Note: =====================================================================

Type called "InstructionDefinition":
    opcode as Integer
    mnemonic as String
    operand_types as List[String]
    stack_input_count as Integer
    stack_output_count as Integer
    execution_cost as Integer
    instruction_category as String
    aott_tier_support as List[Integer]
    side_effects as List[String]

Type called "InstructionEncoding":
    instruction as String
    encoding_format as String
    byte_length as Integer
    operand_positions as List[Integer]
    immediate_encoding as String
    register_encoding as String

Note: =====================================================================
Note: INSTRUCTION SET OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "get_instruction_definition" that takes opcode as Integer returns InstructionDefinition:
    Note: Get instruction definition by opcode
    Note: TODO: Implement instruction definition lookup
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Instruction definition lookup not yet implemented"

Process called "encode_instruction" that takes instruction as String, operands as List[String] returns String:
    Note: Encode instruction with operands to bytecode
    Note: TODO: Implement instruction encoding
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Instruction encoding not yet implemented"

Process called "decode_instruction" that takes bytecode as String, offset as Integer returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Decode bytecode instruction at given offset
    Note: TODO: Implement instruction decoding
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Instruction decoding not yet implemented"

Note: =====================================================================
Note: UTILITY OPERATIONS
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "validate_instruction_set" that returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate instruction set consistency and completeness
    Note: TODO: Implement instruction set validation
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Instruction set validation not yet implemented"

Process called "get_instruction_stack_effect" that takes opcode as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Integer]:
    Note: Get stack input/output effect of instruction
    Note: TODO: Implement stack effect computation
    Throw Errors.NotImplemented with "Stack effect computation not yet implemented"